---
import Base from "../layouts/Base.astro";
import { getCollection } from "astro:content";
const pageTitle = "Personal Website and blog";
const poemPosts = await getCollection("poems");
const blogPosts = await getCollection("posts");
// const reviewPosts = await getCollection("mahabharat");
const allPosts = [...poemPosts, ...blogPosts];
const recentPosts = allPosts
  .sort(
    (a, b) => new Date(b.data.date).getTime() - new Date(a.data.date).getTime()
  )
  .slice(0, 5);
---

<Base title="home">
  <div class="md:grid md:grid-cols-3 bg-[url('/public/background.png')] md:gap-4 m-5 md:text-xl">
    <div
      class="prose bg-[url('/public/background.png')] md:text-lg md:col-span-2 order-first md:text-left border border-dashed border-gray-500 mt-2 mb-2 p-4"
    >
      <p class="pb-2"><b>Welcome, dear visitor, to my personal website!</b></p>
      <p>
        Having a website is a matter of leaving a digital footprint, a way to
        express myself, and a platform to share my thoughts and creations with
        the world. This site is a reflection of who I am, what I do, and what I
        love. It's a space where I can be myself, explore my interests, and
        connect with like-minded individuals.
        I am Hitarth, a tech enthusiast from India. I'm passionate about creativity,
        storytelling, and technology, and this website is my nook on the internet to express that
        passion.
      </p>
      <p>
        Back in 2016, I ventured into the world of digital art. It was a year of
        exploration and creativity, and the result is a collection of digital
        artwork that I'm quite proud of. You can check out my creations right <a
          href="/artwork">here</a
        > on this site. Last but not least, I was the creator of <a
          href="https://tildevarsh.in">~tildevarsh</a
        >, <em>(now defunct)</em>, a vibrant online space where I used to spend a lot of my time. It was a
        wonderful community, and I'd forever cherish the things we did there.
      </p>
      <p>
        So, take a look around, explore, and enjoy your stay. This is my corner
        of the internet, and I'm glad to share it with you.
      </p>
      <hr class="my-2" />
      <blockquote class="text-xl italic font-semibold">
        <svg class="w-8 h-8 text-gray-400 dark:text-gray-600 mb-4" aria-hidden="true" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 18 14">
          <path d="M6 0H2a2 2 0 0 0-2 2v4a2 2 0 0 0 2 2h4v1a3 3 0 0 1-3 3H2a1 1 0 0 0 0 2h1a5.006 5.006 0 0 0 5-5V2a2 2 0 0 0-2-2Zm10 0h-4a2 2 0 0 0-2 2v4a2 2 0 0 0 2 2h4v1a3 3 0 0 1-3 3h-1a1 1 0 0 0 0 2h1a5.006 5.006 0 0 0 5-5V2a2 2 0 0 0-2-2Z"/>
        </svg>
        “We behold what we are, and we are what we behold.”
      </blockquote>


    </div>
    <div
      class="border border-dashed border-gray-500 md:col-span-1 mt-2 mb-2 p-4"
    >
      <div class="serifs">Recent Posts</div>
      {
        recentPosts.map((post) => (
          <div class="md:text-lg my-4">
            {" "}
            <a class="recents" href={post.collection + "/" + post.slug}>
              {" "}
              {post.data.title}
            </a>{" "}
          </div>
        ))
      }

<hr>
       <br> <div class="serifs">Get in touch</div><br>

        <ul>
          <li class="">
            <b>Email:</b> hittarth91 [at] gmail [dot] com / PGP Key
          </li><br>
          <li class="">
            <b>IRC:</b> Find me as gtlsgamr @ #gnulinuxindia:libera.chat and @ #tildevarsh:libera.chat
          </li><br>
          <li class=""><b>Connect </b>on <a href="https://github.com/gtlsgamr">Github</a> and <a href="https://github.com/gtlsgamr">Gitlab</a></li>
        </ul>


    </div>
  </div>
</Base>

<style>
  * {
    font-family: "Droid Serif", serif;
  }
  .serifs {
    font-family: "Playfair Display", serif;
    font-weight: 300;
    font-style: italic;
  }
  .recents {
    color: rgb(49, 49, 49) !important;
  }
</style>
